  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Identify the hypotenuse",
      "content": "Angle $B$ is the right angle, so $AB$ and $BC$ are the legs, and $AC$ is the hypotenuse."
    },
    {
      "title": "Use the right-triangle theorem",
      "content": "Use $AC^2=AB^2+BC^2$:\n$$\nAC^2=(7\\sqrt{41})^2+(24\\sqrt{41})^2\n$$\n$$\nAC^2=49\\cdot41+576\\cdot41\n$$\n$$\nAC^2=625\\cdot41\n$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Find the side length",
      "content": "Since $625=25^2$,\n$$\nAC=\\sqrt{625\\cdot41}=25\\sqrt{41}\n$$\nThe answer is <strong>B</strong>."
    }
  ]
